genresAdvancedInfo.name: indonesian experimental
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Indonesian experimental music is a genre that encompasses a wide range of experimental styles and techniques. It often incorporates unconventional instruments, sounds, and structures, and can range from ambient and minimalist to noisy and chaotic. Indonesian experimental music is characterized by its willingness to push boundaries and explore new sonic territories.
